This paper deals with pattern mining, which is a subfield of data mining and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on constraints for pattern selection, which is a common topic in the subfield of database systems (cs.DB) and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also introduces a new algorithm for generating patterns that satisfy nonmonotonic constraints, which is relevant to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of delta-measure, which is a concept from information theory (cs.IT).
